In late September, Google began providing free Wi-Fi access around areas in the city of San Francisco. It then announced itself to be one of the bidders in the city's mayor's invitation to companies, to bid for a plan to offer Free Wi-Fi in San Francisco. Google filed 40 minutes before the deadline. Speculators however donot feel that providing Free Wi-Fi around other cities of USA is currently on Google's agenda
